                  java.lang.String renterId,
                  Rating rating)
           throws RatingAlreadyExistsException,

        Rate the provider. Rating is an integer from 0 to 5. The rating value is added to officeProviderRatingsMap. if it is found throw RatingAlreadyExistsException. ProviderId is checked as well if it's not found - ProfileNotFoundException is thrown
        Parameters:

      • createOfficeSpace

        void createOfficeSpace(AccessToken accToken,
                       OfficeSpace officeSpace,
                       java.lang.String providerId)
                throws OfficeSpaceAlreadyExistException,
                       AccessException,
                       AccessNotAllowedException
        Creates a new OfficeSpace: add office space to officeSpaceMap; check if it exists already and throws OfficeSpaceAlreadyExistException if it is. If authentication fails - throw AccessException. Rating Field is initialized here. Note: officeSpaceId has to be generated first! Check for officeSpaceIds and providerId in the id buckets, if this check fails throw the
        Parameters:
        accToken - - access token
        officeSpace - the office space
        providerId - - provider id
        Throws:
        OfficeSpaceAlreadyExistException - the office space already exist exception
        AccessException - the access exception
        AccessNotAllowedException
